dex1: 'When attacked by bird Pokemon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.'
dex2: 'It's easy to catch, and it grows quickly, making it one of the top recommendations for novice Pokemon Trainers.'

dex1: Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn't move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.
dex2: 'Its shell is hard, but it's still just a bug shell. It's been known to break, so intense battles with it should be avoided.'

dex1: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.
dex2: 'When attacked by other Pokemon, it defends itself by scattering its poisonous scales and fluttering its wings.'

dex1: 'Its incisors continue growing until its death. If its Trainer doesn't offer it a file to gnaw on, it will gnaw on door frames, table legs, and so on.'
dex2: 'With their strong capacity for survival, they can live in dirty places without concern. Left unchecked, their numbers multiply rapidly.'

dex1: 'Its hind feet are webbed, so it's a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.'
dex2: 'Its disposition is far more violent than its looks would suggest. Don't let your hand get too close to its face, as it could bite your hand clean off.'

dex1: Its short wings make it inept at flying. It moves about hurriedly and pecks at Bug-type Pokemon in the tall grass.
dex2: Farmers whose fields are troubled by bug Pokemon appreciate Spearow for its vigorous appetite and look after it.

dex1: It's tough and has excellent stamina. It has no problem flying continuously for a whole day carrying a heavy load.
dex2: Drawings of a Pokemon resembling Fearow can be seen in murals from deep in ancient history.

dex1: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
dex2: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.

dex1: 'It unleashes electric shocks that can reach 100,000 volts. When agitated, it can knock out even an Indian elephant.'
dex2: 'It becomes aggressive when it has electricity stored up. At such times, even its Trainer has to take care to avoid being attacked.'

dex1: It can roll its body into a ball. It moves through the desert by rolling at high speeds.
dex2: 'It usually makes its home in deserts and arid zones, where rain does not fall. It digs holes to catch Bug-type Pokemon.'

dex1: 'Although they are sharp, its claws and spikes often break off. They grow back the next day, so it is not bothered by the temporary loss.'
dex2: 'It uses its claws to climb trees and then curls its body into a spiny ball, ready to drop onto any prey that appears.'

dex1: 'Its adorable behavior and appearance make it popular with men and women, young and old. Its numbers are few, however.'
dex2: 'On nights with a full moon, they gather together and dance. The surrounding area is enveloped in an abnormal magnetic field.'

dex1: They don't like to reveal themselves in front of people. They live quietly in packs deep in the mountains.
dex2: 'According to tradition, people who see a pair of Clefable skipping by can look forward to a happy marriage.'

dex1: 'Its beautiful fur and tails have made it very popular. As it grows, its tails split to form more tails.'
dex2: From its mouth spew flames that seem to resemble the spirits of the deceased. Some people mistakenly think this fire is a ghost.

dex1: Legend has it that this mystical Pokemon was formed when nine saints coalesced into one.
dex2: 'Said to live for a thousand years, this Pokemon uses its supernatural abilities to manipulate fire. It can burn its prey to a crisp as it pleases.'

dex1: 'It hugely inflates its stomach and sings a mysterious melody. If you hear this melody, you'll become sleepy right away.'
dex2: 'Jigglypuff possess a vocal range that exceeds 12 octaves, but each individual's singing skill depends on its own effort.'

dex1: It sheds its fine fur when the seasons change. The fur is gathered and spun into a luxurious yarn.
dex2: 'As it inhales, it expands...and expands...and expands. Wigglytuff compete to see which one can inflate itself the most.'

dex1: 'It sleeps in caves during the day. It has no eyes, so to check its surroundings while flying, it emits ultrasonic waves.'
dex2: 'When exposed to sunlight, they suffer burns. The frequency of their ultrasonic waves can differ slightly from colony to colony.'

dex1: 'Its thick fangs are hollow like straws, making them unexpectedly fragile. These fangs are specialized for sucking blood.'
dex2: 'Sometimes they drink so much blood, they can't fly anymore. Then they fall to the ground and become food for other Pokemon.'

dex1: 'No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.'
dex2: Mushrooms called tochukaso sprout from its back. They can be dried and powdered to make a medicine used to extend life.

dex1: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.
dex2: 'It scatters toxic spores from its mushroom cap. Once harvested, these spores can be steeped and boiled down to prepare herbal medicines.'

dex1: It chews on plant roots underground. Farmers whose vegetables are vulnerable find it can be quite a pest.
dex2: Many farmers cherish and nurture Diglett because its droppings enrich the soil it lives in.

dex1: This set of triplets moves cooperatively. It's the power of teamwork that enables this Pokemon to dig to a depth of 60 miles.
dex2: 'Despite the closeness between this Pokemon and farmers and other people, no one has ever seen the parts of it concealed underground.'

dex1: 'It lies around all day, becoming active near dusk. At night, it wanders the city in search of loose change.'
dex2: It loves shiny things. It often fights with Murkrow over prey they're both trying to catch.

dex1: It has a violent temperament. It will attack anything that looks it in the eye. Its sharp claws inflict deep wounds.
dex2: 'It has a high opinion of itself, although not to the same extent as the Alolan Persian. It's quite difficult to make friends with this Pokemon.'

dex1: 'As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon is troubled by constant headaches. The more pain it's in, the more powerful its psychokinesis becomes.'

dex1: 'It is said that the red part of its forehead grants supernatural powers to those who possess one, so it was over-hunted in the past.'
dex2: It swims along the banks of lakes and catches fish Pokemon. It takes them to the shore and quietly eats them up.

dex1: 'It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages, and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.'
dex2: 'Its raging tires it out and causes it to fall asleep, but the anger resonating in its dreams causes it to wake up—which infuriates it all over again.'

dex1: 'It has been known to become so angry that it dies as a result. Its face looks peaceful in death, however.'
dex2: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poke Ball.

dex1: 'It's both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.'
dex2: 'It looks cute, but when you approach another Trainer's Growlithe, it will bark at you and bite.'

dex1: 'Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokemon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.'
dex2: The fire burning inside its body serves as the energy to fuel it as it runs great distances. It appears in many legends.

dex1: 'The swirl on its belly is its internal organs showing through. If the swirl is tinged white, that means it's affected by some disease.'
dex2: It's still not very good at walking. Its Trainers should train this Pokemon to walk every day.

dex1: 'Although it can live on land, it prefers to stay in the water, where it has fewer natural enemies.'
dex2: It marches over the land in search of bug Pokemon to eat. Then it takes them underwater so it can dine on them where it's safe.

dex1: Poliwrath in the Alola region are strong swimmers that use the breaststroke. Many children learn to swim by imitating Poliwrath.
dex2: 'Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.'

dex1: 'It sleeps 18 hours a day. Even while sleeping, it will teleport itself to treetops and pick and eat berries there.'
dex2: 'It can teleport itself to safety while it's asleep, but when it wakes, it doesn't know where it is, so it panics.'

dex1: A theory exists that this Pokemon was a young boy who couldn't control his psychic powers and ended up transformed into this Pokemon.
dex2: Kadabra's presence infests televisions and monitors with creepy shadows that bring bad luck.

dex1: 'It is said to have an IQ of approximately 5,000. Its overflowing psychokinetic powers cause headaches to anyone nearby.'
dex2: 'Its brain cells continue to increase in number until its death. The older the Alakazam, the larger its head.'

dex1: 'It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.'
dex2: 'With its superhuman strength, it's able to throw a hundred people all at the same time. Its strength comes from lifting Graveler every day.'

dex1: 'As a result of its continual workouts, it has developed tremendous power. It uses that power to help people with their work.'
dex2: It willingly assists with hard labor because it knows the work is good training for its muscles.

dex1: It unleashes megaton-level punches that send opponents flying clear over the horizon.
dex2: It can lift heavy loads with the greatest of ease. It can even heft dump trucks. But its clumsy fingers prevent it from doing any precision work.

dex1: 'They can be found lying dehydrated on beaches, but they are often still alive. When soaked in water, they will revive.'
dex2: 'It drifts in shallow seas, such as the areas near beaches. If you get bitten or stabbed by its toxic tentacles, rush to the hospital.'

dex1: 'Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles. The longer one has been alive, the fewer tentacles it will have.'
dex2: 'Although these Pokemon are rare, when a large outbreak of them occurs, all fish Pokemon disappear from the surrounding sea.'

dex1: 'Its round body makes it easy to pick up, but it is hard and heavy. It's dangerous to play with them as if they were snowballs.'
dex2: There are plenty of them to be found along any road. A scholar with too much free time once counted a hundred of them along a single route.

dex1: Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly.
dex2: 'This slow-footed Pokemon moves by curling up and rolling instead of walking. With enough momentum, its speed can exceed 60 mph.'

dex1: 'Its body can survive dynamite blasts without a single scratch, but it hates rain and humidity.'
dex2: 'Once a year, this Pokemon molts, and its shed shell returns to the soil. This process creates enriched soil, so farmers collect the shells.'

dex1: 'Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn't really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn't particularly bothered.'
dex2: Alolan home cooking involves drying Slowpoke tails and then simmering them into a salty stew.

dex1: 'It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder's poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.'
dex2: 'Whenever Shellder bites down hard on its tail, it gives Slowbro a flash of inspiration...which it forgets a moment later.'

dex1: They gather in places where electricity is available. They can be found clinging to the steel towers used to support power lines.
dex2: 'It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it's eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.'

dex1: 'When three Magnemite link together, their brains also become one. They do not become three times more intelligent.'
dex2: 'It has about three times the electrical power of Magnemite. For some reason, outbreaks of this Pokemon happen when lots of sunspots appear.'

dex1: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokemon's numbers have been decreasing in recent years.
dex2: 'It was born from sludge transformed by exposure to X-rays from the moon. When its internal load of germs decreases, it dies.'

dex1: 'The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that's a good thing.'
dex2: 'After recent environmental improvements, this Pokemon is now hardly seen at all. People speculate that it may go extinct at some point.'

dex1: 'The hardness of its shell surpasses the hardness of a diamond. In days gone by, people used the shells to make shields.'
dex2: This Pokemon's tongue is always hanging out. It uses its tongue with great dexterity to dig up sand from the seabed in its search for food.

dex1: Its hard shell cannot be shattered—not even by a bomb. The contents of the shell remain unknown.
dex2: Excavation of the tombs of ancient hunting tribes has turned up many spears tipped with spikes that had fallen off this Pokemon's shell.

dex1: 'Should a strange light be seen flickering in an abandoned building, Gastly is lurking there.'
dex2: 'Although Gastly is barely visible, when it's near, a faint sweet smell lingers.'

dex1: It strikes at humans from total darkness. Those licked by its cold tongue grow weaker with each passing day until they die.
dex2: It fears the light and revels in the dark. It may be on the verge of extinction in cities that stay brightly lit at night.

dex1: 'Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.'
dex2: 'It apparently wishes for a traveling companion. Since it was once human itself, it tries to create one by taking the lives of other humans.'

dex1: 'A Pokemon that nourishes itself by eating dreams, it is thought to share common ancestry with Munna and Musharna.'
dex2: 'It finds really fun dreams tasty. When it makes friends with people, it may show them the most delicious dreams it's ever eaten.'

dex1: 'While it is an extremely dangerous Pokemon, people who are in need of a good, sound sleep call it their savior.'
dex2: 'As a matter of course, it makes anyone it meets fall asleep and has a taste of their dreams. Anyone having a good dream, it carries off.'

dex1: Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.
dex2: 'Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokemon. It's often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.'

dex1: Each of its heads has its own will. They use telepathy to discuss their plans before coming to a joint decision.
dex2: 'When the time comes, one of its three heads falls off. Before long, the fallen head grows into an Exeggcute.'

dex1: 'When it thinks of its deceased mother, it weeps loudly. Mandibuzz that hear its cries will attack it from the air.'
dex2: 'The skull it wears on its head is that of its dead mother. According to some, it will evolve when it comes to terms with the pain of her death.'

dex1: 'Originally, it was weak and timid. After evolution, its temperament becomes violent, and it begins to wield bones as weapons.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon is out for vengeance on its natural enemy, Mandibuzz. It throws bones like boomerangs to try to take it down.'

dex1: The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokemon.
dex2: 'Not only are these Pokemon fast runners, they're also few in number, so anyone who finds one must be lucky indeed.'

dex1: Kangaskhan's maternal love is so deep that it will brave death to protect its offspring.
dex2: The child in its pouch leaves home after roughly three years. That is the only time the mother is heard to cry wildly.

dex1: 'When the weather grows warm, they form groups and swim upriver. This sight serves as a poetic reminder that spring has arrived.'
dex2: 'Spellbound by the length of its horn and the beauty of its fins, many strange Trainers raise Goldeen and nothing but Goldeen.'

dex1: 'When the weather grows cold, its whole body flushes a deep red. This sight serves as a poetic reminder that autumn has arrived.'
dex2: Trainers who are crazy for Seaking are divided into horn enthusiasts and fin enthusiasts. The two groups do not get along well.

dex1: 'Large numbers of these Pokemon make their home at the seaside. At night, a strange red glow radiates from the center of their bodies.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon gets nibbled on by Lumineon and others. Thanks to its red core, it regenerates fast, so it's unconcerned by their snack attacks.'

dex1: Its shining core is thought to receive and transmit enigmatic signals. It has been known to cause headaches in those who approach it.
dex2: 'Its unusual body shape, reminiscent of abstract art, led local people to spread rumors that this Pokemon may be an invader from outer space.'

dex1: 'It confuses its prey with its quick, ninja-like movements. Then, in an instant, it cleaves them with its scythes.'
dex2: 'While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.'

dex1: Half of all sudden blackouts are caused by Electabuzz gathering at electric power plants and gobbling up electricity.
dex2: Electricity leaks from it in amounts far greater than the amount of electricity it eats.

dex1: 'When it's tired, it leaps into the mouth of a volcano and soaks its body in magma to ease its weariness. Its body burns at 2,192 degrees F.'
dex2: 'When angered, it spouts brilliant fire from all over its body. It doesn't calm down until its opponent has burned to ash.'

dex1: 'It grips its prey in its pincers and splits them apart. Although it is a powerful Pokemon, it can't deal with the cold.'
dex2: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.

dex1: 'Historically, people in areas all over the world have ridden Tauros, but the practice is said to have started in Alola.'
dex2: 'Although it's known to be a fierce Pokemon, Tauros in the Alola region are said to possess a measure of calmness.'

dex1: 'Although weak and helpless, this Pokemon is incredibly fertile. They exist in such multitudes, you'll soon grow tired of seeing them.'
dex2: 'Its reckless leaps make it easy pickings for predators. On the bright side, many Pokemon enjoy longer life spans, thanks to Magikarp.'

dex1: 'A tale is told of a town that angered Gyarados. Before the sun rose the next day, flames utterly consumed the town, leaving not a trace behind.'
dex2: There are people who swear that any place Gyarados appears is fated for destruction.

dex1: 'Its high intelligence enables it to comprehend human speech. When it's in a good mood, it sings in its beautiful voice.'
dex2: 'These Pokemon were once near extinction due to poaching. Following protective regulations, there is now an overabundance of them.'

dex1: It can reorganize its cells to make itself into a duplicate of anything it sees. The quality of the duplicate depends on the individual.
dex2: 'With its astonishing capacity for metamorphosis, it can get along with anything. It does not get along well with its fellow Ditto.'

dex1: 'Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.'
dex2: Current studies show it can evolve into an incredible eight different species of Pokemon.

dex1: Its cells are composed of units much like water molecules. It lives close to water and is often mistaken for a mermaid.
dex2: 'Blending in with the water and erasing all signs of its presence, it patiently waits for its prey, fish Pokemon.'

dex1: 'They send out electrical charges of about 10,000 volts. Because they are high-strung, it can be difficult to grow close to them.'
dex2: 'When its fur stands on end, that's a sign it's about to give off a jolt of electricity. Take care, as sometimes lightning strikes next to it, too.'

dex1: 'When it catches prey or finds berries, it breathes fire on them until they're well done, and then it gobbles them up.'
dex2: 'Its average body temperature is between 1,300 and 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. In its internal flame sac, temperatures reach 3,000 degrees.'

dex1: 'Roughly 20 years ago, it was artificially created, utilizing the latest technology of the time.'
dex2: 'It can convert its body into digital data, which enables it to enter cyberspace.'

dex1: A Pokemon from the age of the dinosaurs. It used its sawlike fangs to shred its prey before eating them.
dex2: 'In ancient times, it ruled the skies. A widely accepted theory is that it went extinct due to a large meteor impact.'

dex1: Its stomach is said to be incomparably strong. Even Muk's poison is nothing more than a hint of spice on Snorlax's tongue.
dex2: It eats nearly 900 pounds of food every day. It starts nodding off while eating—and continues to eat even while it's asleep.

dex1: It grows by molting repeatedly. Boots made from the tanned cast-off skin are a super luxury item.
dex2: 'After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.'

dex1: It has long been thought that its crystalline orbs are imbued with the power to control the weather.
dex2: 'From time immemorial, it has been venerated by agricultural peoples as an entity able to control the weather.'

dex1: 'This Pokemon saved a shipwrecked man, taking him to a remote island—a paradise occupied solely by Dragonite.'
dex2: 'Incur the wrath of this normally calm Pokemon at your peril, because it will smash everything to smithereens before it's satisfied.'

dex1: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.
dex2: 'They communicate with one another using bodily fluids that give off odors. When they're angry, their odor smells sour.'

dex1: 'While it's believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokemon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.'
dex2: 'In battle, it throws punches with all four arms. The power of each individual blow is piddly, so it aims to win by quantity rather than quality.'

dex1: 'It waits intently until its preferred prey, Cutiefly, gets caught in its web. In fact, it's quite a patient Pokemon.'
dex2: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokemon.

dex1: There are some areas where people use the string Ariados spins for their own weaving. The resulting cloth is popular for its strength.
dex2: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

dex1: 'Both its legs became wings, and as a result, it can't move well on the ground. All it can do is crawl around.'
dex2: 'Silent and swift in its four-winged flight, it bites down on its prey before they realize what's happening. In a heartbeat, it drains their blood.'

dex1: Its two antennae were originally fins. It discharges electricity to stun its prey before attacking.
dex2: It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

dex1: 'Should you peer into the ocean at night and see a light shining like the stars, that is Lanturn.'
dex2: This Pokemon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

dex1: 'It is not yet skilled at controlling electricity. If you take your eyes off it, it may shock itself.'
dex2: 'Despite this Pokemon's cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.'

dex1: 'On late nights illuminated by shooting stars, it gazes intently skyward, as if thinking of its home.'
dex2: 'Because of its silhouette, it's believed to be a star reborn. For some reason, it loves Minior.'

dex1: 'It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.'
dex2: 'It moves by bouncing along. As it moves a lot, it sweats, and its body gives off a sweet aroma.'

dex1: 'To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates.'
dex2: 'Apparently, the larger the green parts of this Pokemon, the more collectors value it. It's a particular favorite among elderly people.'

dex1: 'They gather on moonlit nights to form a large chorus. Their cries sound angry and not at all pleasant, but they are certainly distinctive.'
dex2: 'It's the leader of Poliwag and Poliwhirl. When Politoed roars, they all cower in fear.'

dex1: It can instantaneously sense its opponent's movements by feeling air currents with its fine fur.
dex2: 'It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.'

dex1: 'When this Pokemon becomes angry, its pores secrete a poisonous sweat, which it sprays at its opponent's eyes.'
dex2: 'With its black fur, it blends into the darkness. It bides its time, and when prey appears, this Pokemon goes for its throat, and then eats it.'

dex1: 'They awaken at dusk and take wing in the twilight, leading to the expression, “Get home before the Murkrow fly.”'
dex2: 'Seen as a symbol of bad luck, it's generally disliked. Yet it gives presents—objects that sparkle or shine—to Trainers it's close to.'

dex1: 'A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon is so famed for its intellect that a proverb still persists in some regions: “When in doubt, ask Slowking.”'

dex1: It will use any means necessary to frighten people and absorb their life energy. It practices constantly to hone its skill in causing fear.
dex2: 'If you hear a sobbing sound emanating from a vacant room, it's undoubtedly a bit of mischief from Misdreavus.'

dex1: 'Despite its intimidating face, it's quite cowardly. Its desperate attempts to appear threatening make it popular with people.'
dex2: Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokemon tends to sleep half the day.

dex1: 'Its well-developed lower jaw and heavy fangs are its weapons. As long as it's not provoked, it rarely bites.'
dex2: 'More timid than Snubbull, this Pokemon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.'

dex1: 'It uses its wings to adjust its body temperature. Otherwise, its metal body would become too hot and melt in the heat of battle.'
dex2: 'Once it has identified an enemy, this Pokemon smashes it mercilessly with pincers hard as steel.'

dex1: 'It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.'
dex2: It uses its claws to poke holes in eggs so it can slurp out the insides. Breeders consider it a scourge and will drive it away or eradicate it.

dex1: 'Coral branches grow from its head. They break off quite easily, but they grow back in about three days.'
dex2: 'Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokemon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.'

dex1: 'Although it naturally prefers colder locales, Delibird in Alola seem able to withstand the heat to a certain extent.'
dex2: 'It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokemon, so it's always scrounging around for more food.'

dex1: 'Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords.'
dex2: 'Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pokemon prefers to stay put in its nest.'

dex1: 'For the purposes of planetary development, Porygon was updated with the most cutting-edge technology available.'
dex2: Porygon was updated to a new version in readiness for planetary development. But that dream remains unrealized as yet.

dex1: The unique creations produced by each Smeargle are painted using the fluid that oozes from its tail. This is how it marks its territory.
dex2: 'It draws symbols all over the place to mark its territory. In towns with many Smeargle, the walls are covered in graffiti.'

dex1: 'When it's in a house, electrical outlets serve as its baby bottles. It sucks down electricity.'
dex2: This Pokemon is constantly fighting with Togedemaru that try to steal its electricity. It's a pretty even match.

dex1: 'Many of these Pokemon can be seen in areas with volcanic activity. Feeding can get them so excited, they exhale flames of 1,100 degrees F.'
dex2: A famous potter lives with a Magby. Apparently its soft flames produce fine works.

dex1: 'Its milk is high in calories and packed with nutrients. Therefore, if you drink too much of it, you may wind up with a body like Miltank's.'
dex2: 'Most people raise it for its milk, but it's quite tough and strong, so it's also well suited for battle.'

dex1: 'Even the most ferocious Pokemon become calm when they eat Blissey's egg, which is said to be filled with happiness.'
dex2: 'Its fluffy fur coat acts as a sensor, enabling it to read the feelings of people and Pokemon.'

dex1: Its hollow bones enhance its lightness. It spreads its wings to the wind and soars away into the sky.
dex2: 'Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they're circling, the ocean is sure to be teeming with fish Pokemon.'

dex1: Its spacious beak is large enough for a small child to fit right inside.
dex2: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.

dex1: It moves as if skating on the surface of the water. It often fights with Dewpider over food.
dex2: 'When this Pokemon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its head. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokemon.'

dex1: It intimidates enemies with the eye-like patterns on its antennae. Its four wings allow it to fly in any direction.
dex2: 'Its wings and antennae don't cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.'

dex1: 'It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.'
dex2: 'Their daily routine consists of training together first thing in the morning, eating and napping in the afternoon, and then more training afterward.'

dex1: 'It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training Makuhita.'
dex2: They love to compare their freakish strength— strength enough to send a truck flying with a single slap.

dex1: 'The magnet in Nosepass's nose provides an unerring compass, making it an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.'
dex2: 'It uses powerful magnetism to drag its prey toward it. It's also been known to pull in metal, which it collects and uses to protect itself.'

dex1: 'It's a fiend for gemstones, so it stalks Carbink. Unfortunately, Gabite almost always grabs them first.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.'

dex1: Each school has its own territory. Any intruders are mercilessly attacked with fangs bared.
dex2: 'If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they're rather cowardly.'

dex1: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.
dex2: 'It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokemon became a victim of overfishing.'

dex1: It loves to startle people. It fills itself up with seawater and plays by bouncing around like a ball.
dex2: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

dex1: 'Wailord pursue their prey in pods. With their large mouths, they can swallow entire schools of Wishiwashi whole.'
dex2: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

dex1: Coal is the source of Torkoal's energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.
dex2: 'If the fire burning within its shell goes out, it will die. Those who wish to raise one in their home must always keep something flammable at hand.'

dex1: 'Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it's walking in a straight line.'
dex2: Each and every Spinda has a slightly different configuration of spots. There are collectors who enjoy the tiny differences in their spot patterns.

dex1: It can live for a week without eating a thing. It waits patiently at the bottom of its nest for prey to appear.
dex2: 'As it digs through the sand, its giant jaws crush any rocks that obstruct its path. It builds a funnel-shaped nest.'

dex1: 'Rather than using its underdeveloped wings for flight, it rubs them together, producing ultrasonic waves to attack its enemies.'
dex2: 'To help make its wings grow, it dissolves quantities of prey in its digestive juices and guzzles them down every day.'

dex1: 'The flapping of its wings sounds something like singing. Those lured by the sound are enveloped in a sandstorm, becoming Flygon's prey.'
dex2: This Pokemon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

dex1: 'Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey's location.'
dex2: 'Its slippery body is hard to grasp, so much so that there are festivals where people compete to see how many they can catch barehanded.'

dex1: 'A glutton that devours anything that moves, it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps, lying in wait for prey.'
dex2: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.

dex1: 'A tough Pokemon that is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn't popular.'
dex2: 'Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokemon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.'

dex1: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokemon of all.
dex2: 'It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people's minds and hearts.'

dex1: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.
dex2: 'Its form changes on its own, due to its cells' sensitive reactions to temperature and humidity.'

dex1: 'Long ago, superstitions were spread about it, saying it brought disaster. This fed a hatred of it, and it was driven deep into the mountains.'
dex2: 'Although it's said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokemon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.'

dex1: Their numbers seem to have rapidly increased in Alola. Custom has it that houses where Snorunt live will be prosperous for generations to come.
dex2: 'It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.'

dex1: 'Legend says a boulder on an icy mountain absorbed the distress and regrets of a stranded mountaineer, giving rise to Glalie.'
dex2: 'Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they're in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.'

dex1: 'Its form has remained the same for one hundred million years. Its body is filled with fat, so it can withstand the water pressure of the deep sea.'
dex2: 'It was fortuitously discovered during a deep sea expedition. Its teeth have atrophied, so it now survives on microscopic organisms it sucks up.'

dex1: 'If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when Pelipper snatch them up.'
dex2: 'Loving couples have a soft spot for this Pokemon, so honeymoon hotels often release this Pokemon into their pools.'

dex1: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.
dex2: 'With its steel-hard stone head, it headbutts indiscriminately. This is because of the stress it feels at being unable to fly.'

dex1: 'The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.'
dex2: 'They lurk deep within caves—motionless, neither eating nor drinking. Why they don't die is not known.'

dex1: 'When angered, it loses all sense of itself and destroys everything around it. The destruction will continue until Salamence has tired itself out.'
dex2: 'It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.'

dex1: Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.
dex2: 'With magnetic traction, it pulls its opponents in close. When they're in range, it slashes them with its rear claws.'

dex1: 'When two Beldum link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.'
dex2: 'It adores magnetic minerals, so it pursues Nosepass at speeds exceeding 60 mph.'

dex1: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then the teeth in the mouth on its stomach chew the prey to bits.
dex2: 'A linkage of two Metang, this Pokemon can perform any calculation in a flash by utilizing parallel processing in its four brains.'

dex1: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.
dex2: 'In rock layers where Cranidos fossils are found, the fossilized trunks of trees snapped in two are also often found.'

dex1: 'The result of repeated headbutts is a skull grown thick and hard. However, its brain has shrunk in size compared with Cranidos's.'
dex2: Records exist of a revived fossil that evolved into Rampardos. It proceeded to escape and then destroy a skyscraper with a headbutt.

dex1: 'Many fossils of this Pokemon have been found, but almost none have shown signs of damage to the face.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it's thought.'

dex1: 'While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.'
dex2: It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together— seemingly from after they'd fought to the finish.

dex1: 'For the most part, it makes its home along the seashore. Its color and form differ according to its habitat and the quality of its food.'
dex2: 'Purple mucus sticks to the hands of anyone who touches it. Take care, as the substance is troublesome to wash off.'

dex1: 'It has strong regenerative capabilities. Even if parts of it are bitten off by fish Pokemon, it will return to normal within a few hours.'
dex2: 'Plankton, invisible to the naked eye, is its main food source. It comes onto the land periodically, but the reason for this is not known.'

dex1: Stories go that it grabs the hands of small children and drags them away to the afterlife. It dislikes heavy children.
dex2: 'If for some reason its body bursts, its soul spills out with a screaming sound.'

dex1: 'There was once an incident in which a man took a trip riding a Drifblim, only to go missing.'
dex2: 'Even while under careful observation, large flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk will inexplicably disappear from view.'

dex1: 'It appears as if from nowhere—muttering incantations, placing curses, and giving people terrifying visions.'
dex2: 'Mismagius have been known to cast spells to make people fall in love, so some people search for this Pokemon as if their life depended on it.'

dex1: 'A single cry from this nocturnal Pokemon, and more than a hundred of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.'
dex2: 'If its Murkrow cronies fail to catch food for it, or if it feels they have betrayed it, it will hunt them down wherever they are and punish them.'

dex1: 'It does not deal well with water, so it lives in dry locales. Since its surroundings tend to lack greenery, it stands out noticeably.'
dex2: 'From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.'

dex1: 'It carries a round white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.'
dex2: 'It's too small to lay eggs yet. As a surrogate, it searches out round white stones.'

dex1: 'It lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat. Even so, when the weather gets cold, it will huddle close with others of its kind.'
dex2: 'It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.'

dex1: 'In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.'
dex2: 'Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it's amassed or Carbink it has caught.'

dex1: It can fly at speeds rivaling jet planes. It dives into flocks of bird Pokemon and gulps the entire flock down whole.
dex2: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.

dex1: 'It needs to consume its own weight in food every day. As far as flavor is concerned, it's indifferent.'
dex2: 'When it finds something that looks like it might be edible, it goes right ahead and swallows it whole. That's why it gets fatter day by day.'

dex1: 'It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokemon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.'
dex2: 'It's tough enough to run right through the night, and it's also a hard worker, but it's still just a youngster.'

dex1: 'Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.'
dex2: They can detect the species of a living being— and its emotions—from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.

dex1: 'It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.'
dex2: 'Its double tail fins propel its energetic jumps. When it breaks the surface of the sea, Wingull swoop down to grab it on the fly.'

dex1: 'With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokemon—its natural predators.'
dex2: This deep-sea Pokemon lives at the bottom of the sea. Its fins haul it over the seabed in search of its favorite food—Starmie.

dex1: 'They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.'
dex2: 'They dwell in cold places. This Pokemon's main food source in Alola is Vulpix and Sandshrew, which they carefully divide among their group.'

dex1: Three units generate magnetism. There have been many mistaken reports of UFO sightings when Magnezone flies through the night sky.
dex2: 'As it zooms through the sky, this Pokemon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.'

dex1: It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.
dex2: 'When it gets excited, it thumps its chest. With every thud, thunder roars and electric sparks shower all around.'

dex1: 'They dwell in volcanic craters. According to what is known, a single pair of male and female Magmortar lives in one volcano.'
dex2: 'From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than 3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to melt when it fires a whole barrage.'

dex1: Its cellular composition is closer to that of a plant than an animal. It uses photosynthesis to produce its energy supply without eating food.
dex2: 'The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.'

dex1: 'It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.'
dex2: 'It freezes its fur into icicles, spiky and sharp, and tackles its prey.'

dex1: 'In order to create a more advanced Pokemon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.'
dex2: 'Its program was modified to facilitate extra-dimensional activities, but that led to noticeably strange behavior.'

dex1: It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.
dex2: 'The main body controls three mobile units called Mini-Noses, which it maneuvers to catch prey.'

dex1: 'When it finds humans or Pokemon it likes, it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den, where they become decorations.'
dex2: 'The soul of a woman lost on a snowy mountain possessed an icicle, becoming this Pokemon. The food it most relishes is the souls of men.'

dex1: 'Because it doesn't yelp, it's extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.'
dex2: 'The long fur surrounding its face functions as radar, enabling it to probe the condition of its battle opponents.'

dex1: Its dense black fur grows continuously. The high cost of keeping its hard fur properly groomed makes this a troublesome Pokemon to train.
dex2: 'This Pokemon obeys its master's orders faithfully. However, it refuses to listen to anything said by a person it doesn't respect.'

dex1: 'Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it's a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.'
dex2: 'With this wise Pokemon, there could be no concern that it would ever attack people. Some parents even trust it to babysit.'

dex1: 'Born deep within the ground, it compares itself with similar species, such as Geodude and Carbink, to settle which has the hardest body.'
dex2: 'The hexagonal cavity is its ear. It walks in the direction of sounds it hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics and topples over.'

dex1: Its orange crystal is a mass of energy. Just one crystal fragment would provide enough fuel for a hundred dump trucks.
dex2: 'It explores caves in search of underground water. It's not comfortable around water, so this Pokemon takes great care in lapping it up.'

dex1: 'The blasts of energy it makes from sunbeams have terrifying power. However, it's not able to fire its blasts at night or on rainy days.'
dex2: 'Known for its hefty horsepower, this Pokemon is a popular partner for construction workers.'

dex1: 'When it finds others of its kind, they all stick together. When enough of them have collected, the mass resembles a cumulonimbus cloud.'
dex2: 'Pillows and beds stuffed with cotton exhaled by Cottonee are soft and puffy, light and airy— altogether top quality.'

dex1: 'It rides on the wind and slips into people's homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton- filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon appears, riding upon the wind. But if the wind gusts up, it'll blow the cotton on this Pokemon's head clean off.'

dex1: 'Although the leaves on its head are bitter enough to cause dizziness, they provide relief from weariness—even more so when boiled.'
dex2: 'By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pokemon can be grown into a fine plump shape.'

dex1: 'No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.'
dex2: 'As soon as it finds a male to be its partner, the beautiful flower on its head darkens, droops, and withers away.'

dex1: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.
dex2: It conceals itself in the sand and chomps down on the legs of any prey that unwarily walk over it. Its favorite food is Trapinch.

dex1: 'They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.'
dex2: 'Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.'

dex1: 'Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.'
dex2: 'After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.'

dex1: 'Based on studies of its skeletal structure, it can apparently dive to ocean depths of over half a mile.'
dex2: 'Reputed to be the ancestor of most turtle Pokemon, it lived in warm seas approximately a hundred million years ago.'

dex1: It constructed its sturdy shell by crunching and swallowing the hard shells or bones of its prey.
dex2: 'Active both on land and in the sea, this Pokemon drags its land-based prey into the water to finish it off.'

dex1: It is the ancestor of all bird Pokemon. Archen itself could not actually fly but moved by hopping from treetop to treetop.
dex2: 'To all appearances flightless, it was able to glide down from tall treetops to snag its prey.'

dex1: 'Although apparently able to fly, they tended to run along the ground, averaging speeds of roughly 25 mph.'
dex2: 'They hunted in flocks. When one Archeops had the prey cornered, another would swoop on it.'

dex1: 'Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with Grimer in hot pursuit.'
dex2: It gorges on trash until its stomach is full. Then it belches toxic gas. An unlucky whiff of gas will put a person in the hospital.

dex1: 'Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.'
dex2: 'For a time, their numbers increased explosively in Alola. Since the arrival of Grimer, their population has decreased dramatically.'

dex1: 'Born of an icicle, this Pokemon uses its frosty breath to make ice crystals, causing snow to fall.'
dex2: It feels pleasantly cool when embraced. This Pokemon is treasured by households in warm regions.

dex1: 'Hot days cause its body to melt. It can be restored by refreezing it, but the process leaves its body slightly warped.'
dex2: 'This Pokemon has existed since the Ice Age. It controls particles of ice, freezes its opponents, and then shatters them with a headbutt.'

dex1: 'Each of its two heads has a brain, and when they are in agreement, it attacks its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.'
dex2: 'Even if it loses one of its heads, it can live relatively problem-free. It makes snow clouds inside its body.'

dex1: 'It glides using its cape-like membrane. Electrical energy scatters from it, shocking its friends and foes alike.'
dex2: It grills berries and bug Pokemon with electric shocks and makes a meal of them. It usually nests in the holes gouged in trees by Pikipek.

dex1: It uses its special mucus to close the wounds of injured Pokemon. The reason for this behavior remains unknown.
dex2: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokemon gather in the area around Alomomola.

dex1: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.
dex2: 'With its sharp claws, this Pokemon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it's a carnivore at heart.'

dex1: 'With its brave disposition, it fears nothing—not even death. Ancient Alolan people respected it, referring to it as “the hero of the sky.”'
dex2: 'It's thought that people disturbed their habitats in the past, so Braviary banded together to fight back.'

dex1: 'It protects its plump posterior with the bones of prey it has consumed. As it grows, it replaces the bones.'
dex2: 'It can't fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it's still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.'

dex1: 'They adorn themselves beautifully with bones. This is supposedly an effort to attract males, but no male Mandibuzz have ever been found.'
dex2: 'It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokemon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.'

dex1: 'This amiable Pokemon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.'
dex2: 'When it's excited, its temperature can double, spiking hormone production in its body.'

dex1: 'From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.'
dex2: 'It will not tolerate other Fletchinder entering its territory, which has a radius of several miles.'

dex1: Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.
dex2: 'It zooms directly at its prey at flight speeds of close to 310 mph, while fiery embers scatter from gaps in its feathers.'

dex1: 'It grows up imitating the behavior of Pangoro, which it looks up to as a leader.'
dex2: 'There's no point to the leaf in its mouth, aside from an effort to look cool. It's mischievous, so it's not well suited to inexperienced Trainers.'

dex1: It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro's Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.
dex2: 'From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent's movements. It's eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.'

dex1: 'Its ribbonlike feelers give off an aura that weakens hostility in its prey, causing them to let down their guard. Then it attacks.'
dex2: 'When this Pokemon sights its prey, it swirls its ribbonlike feelers as a distraction. A moment later, it pounces.'

dex1: 'Born from the high temperatures and pressures deep underground, it defends itself by firing beams from the jewel part of its body.'
dex2: 'Although this Pokemon is not especially rare, its glittering, jewel-draped body draws attention from people.'

dex1: 'The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokemon, it's unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.'
dex2: 'Its source of protection is its slimy, germ-laden mucous membrane. Anyone who touches it needs some thorough hand-washing.'

dex1: It has trouble drawing a line between friends and food. It will calmly try to melt and eat even those it gets along well with.
dex2: 'This Pokemon's mucous can dissolve anything. Toothless, it sprays mucous on its prey. Once they're nicely dissolved, it slurps them up.'

dex1: 'An amazingly friendly Pokemon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.'
dex2: 'It gets picked on because it's meek. But then, whoever teased it gets to feel the full force of its horns and a good swatting from its thick tail.'

dex1: This even-tempered Pokemon has a habit of collecting keys. It will sneak into people's homes to steal their keys.
dex2: 'It inserts its horn into chinks in metal, absorbing metal ions. For some reason, it collects keys.'

dex1: These Pokemon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.
dex2: 'According to legend, medicine to cure any illness can be made by plucking the green leaves on its head, brewing them, and boiling down the liquid.'

dex1: 'This Pokemon is said to devour anyone daring to ravage the forest. To the creatures dwelling in the forest, it offers great kindness.'
dex2: 'Through its roots, it exerts control over other trees. A deadly curse falls upon anyone cutting down trees in forests where Trevenant dwell.'

dex1: 'This is Zygarde's form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.'
dex2: It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.

dex1: 'This wary Pokemon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.'
dex2: 'Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.'

dex1: 'A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.'
dex2: It throws sharp feathers called blade quills at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.

dex1: 'It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.'
dex2: 'Although basically cool and cautious, when it's caught by surprise, it's seized by panic.'

dex1: 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.'
dex2: It doesn't allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.

dex1: 'At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokemon spits fire.'
dex2: 'It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.'

dex1: 'This Pokemon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it's not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.'
dex2: 'After hurling ferocious punches and flinging furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by spewing fire from around its navel.'

dex1: 'This Pokemon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.'
dex2: This Pokemon can control water bubbles. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big bubbles.

dex1: 'A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.'
dex2: 'It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.'

dex1: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.
dex2: Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokemon's Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.

dex1: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.
dex2: 'This Pokemon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.'

dex1: 'It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.'
dex2: 'By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.'

dex1: 'When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.'
dex2: 'Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.'

dex1: 'With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.'
dex2: 'It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.'

dex1: 'When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it's always snoozing by nightfall.'
dex2: 'It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it's diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokemon boasts incredible patience.'

dex1: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.
dex2: They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokemon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokemon.

dex1: 'Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.'
dex2: 'From the food it digests, it generates electricity, and it stores this energy in its electric sac.'

dex1: 'It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.'
dex2: It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokemon with shocking beams of electrical energy.

dex1: 'While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.'
dex2: 'It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.'

dex1: 'It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokemon evolved and grew fur.'
dex2: 'It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.'

dex1: 'It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.'
dex2: This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.

dex1: 'It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it's able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.'
dex2: Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads of people who have auras resembling those of flowers.

dex1: 'It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.'
dex2: Some of Ribombee's pollen puffs are highly nutritious. They are sometimes sold as supplements.

dex1: 'It's considered to be a good Pokemon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.'
dex2: This Pokemon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.

dex1: 'Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.'
dex2: 'When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.'

dex1: 'When it's in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.'
dex2: 'It's awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.'

dex1: 'It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.'
dex2: It's found crawling on beaches and seafloors. The coral that grows on Corsola's head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokemon.

dex1: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.
dex2: 'Those attacked by Toxapex's poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.'

dex1: The mud stuck to Mudbray's hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.
dex2: 'It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition. Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire all form part of its daily routine.'

dex1: 'It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.'
dex2: 'Its heavy, mud-covered kicks are its best means of attack, and it can reduce large trucks to scrap without breaking a sweat.'

dex1: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.
dex2: 'When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokemon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.'

dex1: 'It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokemon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.'
dex2: 'Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokemon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.'

dex1: 'During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.'
dex2: They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.

dex1: 'It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis's vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.'
dex2: It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.

dex1: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.
dex2: 'As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.'

dex1: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.
dex2: 'It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokemon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.'

dex1: 'It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.'
dex2: 'Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home. It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas that attracts bug Pokemon, then attacks them.'

dex1: 'For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.'
dex2: 'Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of luscious perfumes.'

dex1: 'Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.'
dex2: A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It's an incredibly dangerous Pokemon.

dex1: This immensely dangerous Pokemon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.
dex2: This Pokemon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.

dex1: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.
dex2: 'Although it's too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet's sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.'

dex1: 'The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokemon, this Pokemon is totally fine.'
dex2: This Pokemon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokemon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.

dex1: 'Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.'
dex2: 'A Pokemon known for the beauty of its well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.'

dex1: 'It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.'
dex2: 'Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokemon is a hit with many people.'

dex1: 'Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokemon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it's best suited to veteran Trainers.'
dex2: 'Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokemon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.'

dex1: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.
dex2: 'They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.'

dex1: 'This Pokemon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.'
dex2: 'Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.'

dex1: 'With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.'
dex2: 'It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.'

dex1: 'Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokemon embodies the grudges of the departed.'
dex2: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.

dex1: 'Possessed people controlled by this Pokemon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.'
dex2: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

dex1: 'It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.'
dex2: These Pokemon line the beaches. The sticky mucous that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!

dex1: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokemon has some hidden special power.
dex2: 'Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokemon may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask to restrain its power.'

dex1: 'Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokemon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.'
dex2: 'Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.'

dex1: 'Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.'
dex2: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokemon was born from mutated nanoparticles.

dex1: 'It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.'
dex2: The log it holds was given to it by its parents at birth. It has also been known to cling to the arm of a friendly Trainer.

dex1: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.
dex2: It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.

dex1: 'The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokemon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.'
dex2: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.

dex1: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.
dex2: 'A lonely Pokemon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokemon.'

dex1: 'When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.'
dex2: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder's shell is no match for it.

dex1: 'It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.'
dex2: This Pokemon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.

dex1: 'Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.'
dex2: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokemon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

dex1: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.
dex2: They live in mountains where no trace of humans can be detected. Jangmo-o grow little by little as they battle one another.

dex1: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.
dex2: It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous basis. The scales become harder and sharper each time they're regrown.

dex1: 'When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.'
dex2: 'Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.'

dex1: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.
dex2: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

dex1: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.
dex2: 'As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.'

dex1: 'It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.'
dex2: The guardian deity of Ula'ula is a lazy Pokemon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

dex1: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.
dex2: 'The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.'

dex1: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.
dex2: 'In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It's said to be a Pokemon from another world, but no specific details are known.'

dex1: 'Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.'
dex2: There's something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokemon may come from another world.

dex1: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.
dex2: 'This Pokemon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.'

dex1: 'It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.'
dex2: 'Said to live in another world, this Pokemon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.'

dex1: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.
dex2: 'One of the Ultra Beasts. It's unclear whether or not this Pokemon is sentient, but sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.'

dex1: 'This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.'
dex2: A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.

dex1: 'One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.'
dex2: 'One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.'

dex1: 'One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.'
dex2: 'It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.'

dex1: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.
dex2: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

dex1: 'This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.'
dex2: 'One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.'

dex1: 'It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It's one of the Ultra Beasts.'
dex2: 'A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.'

dex1: 'Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.'
dex2: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.

dex1: 'This artificial Pokemon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.'
dex2: 'Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.'

dex1: 'Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.'
dex2: 'It lurks in the shadows of others, copying their movements and powers. This Pokemon is craven and cowering.'
